  <summary>3/20/1997--Introduced.
Rural Environment Tax Credit Act - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow taxpayers primarily engaged in a farming-related business an investment tax credit for a percentage of: (1) the costs of agricultural environmental property (as defined by this Act); and (2) the amount allowed as a deduction for soil and water conservation expenditures.</summary>
